      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "0.2 - PRINTER SETUP PANEL"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The printer setup panel allows you to create multiple printer"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "configurations which can be used to perform different printing"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "roles. Printer setups are symbolically named. DEFPRN, the default,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "typically performs no formatting functions and is routed to logical"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "device PRN."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The ACTIVE PRINTER field is changed with the SELECT primary or line"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "command.  For example, to activate PAGE1, put an `s` on that line or"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "`s page1` in the primary command field."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
